File: South African coach Pitso Mosimane has beaten Zamalek in a final -- guiding Mamelodi Sundowns of South Africa to a 3-1 aggregate victory in 2016. Khaled DESOUKI / AFP JOHANNESBURG - Pitso Mosimane might still be in the hospital after testing positive for COVID-19 last week but he continues to grab the headlines for his impressive work as Al Ahly coach.
Mosimane scooped the 2020 Most Successful Coach award in Egypt. READ: Ahly, Zamalek face off in historic CAF Champions League final The former Bafana Bafana coach led the Red Devils to their first Caf Champions League title since 2013 and Egyptian Cup. Ahly also won the Egyptian Premier League though when Mosimane took over from Rene Weiler, the title was mathematically secured. In Mosimane's absence, Cavin Johnson has taken care of Al Ahly who have continued where they left off last season, currently topping the log this season after two matches. They also got the defence of their CAF Champions League off to a perfect start with victory in their Last 32 first leg match in midweek.